The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 25 December is 13,658 (1,580.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 20 December, there were 2,083 new confirmed cases (241.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 December, there were 1,055 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 97% (1,028 extra cases).
